	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specified_product_arm  Entity: Product_specification  
   <express_ref linkend="specified_product:arm:Specified_product_arm.Product_specification"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Specified_product_arm.Product_specification">
A <b>Product_specification</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="configuration_item:arm:Configuration_item_arm.Configuration_watched_item"/> that characterizes a product or a set of products in a <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Product_class"/> by a set of specifications.
<note number="1">A <express_ref linkend="specified_product:arm:Specified_product_arm.Product_specification"/> identifies a manufacturable object, or expected as so.
</note>
A <express_ref linkend="specified_product:arm:Specified_product_arm.Product_specification"/> is defined with respect to the <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Product_class"/> it is a member of. 
<note number="2">
The kind of product that is to be manufactured from the data of the <express_ref linkend="specified_product:arm:Specified_product_arm.Product_specification"/>, 
is the kind of product that the "item context" attribute identifies a class of.
</note>
		<note number="3">
The intent of the <express_ref linkend="specified_product:arm:Specified_product_arm.Product_specification"/> entity is the identification of one manufacturable object whereas the intent of <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Product_class"/> is the gathering of products with similar characteristics.
</note>
		<p>
The actual set of <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Specification"/> instances for a <express_ref linkend="specified_product:arm:Specified_product_arm.Product_specification"/> are obtained by the union of the Specification instances grouped in the "defining specification" attribute and 
of the Specification instances related to the considered <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Product_class"/> through a <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Class_specification_association"/> or a <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Class_condition_association"/> with "association type" 'identification' or 'non replaceable standard'.
</p>
		<note number="4">The specification of a <express_ref linkend="specified_product:arm:Specified_product_arm.Product_specification"/> may be incomplete:
there may not be in 'defining specifications' any instance of <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Specification"/> for some <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Specification_category"/> declared as mandatory for the considered <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Product_class"/>.
For these <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Specification_category"/> instances, any specification available in the context of the considered <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Product_class"/> is considered as valid for the manufacturing of the product characterized by the considered <express_ref linkend="specified_product:arm:Specified_product_arm.Product_specification"/>.
</note>
		<example>If the colour is not specified for a given product family, the specified product resulting from the realization of a <express_ref linkend="specified_product:arm:Specified_product_arm.Product_specification"/> associated to the <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Product_class"/> representing the product family may be without paint or painted in any available colour.
</example>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specified_product_arm  Entity: Product_specification  Attribute: version_id 
   <express_ref linkend="specified_product:arm:Specified_product_arm.Product_specification.version_id"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Specified_product_arm.Product_specification.version_id">
the version identifier of the <express_ref linkend="specified_product:arm:Specified_product_arm.Product_specification"/>. 
<p>The "version id" need not be specified for a particular <express_ref linkend="specified_product:arm:Specified_product_arm.Product_specification"/>.</p>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Specified_product_arm.Product_specification.item_context">
the <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Product_class"/> that the <express_ref linkend="specified_product:arm:Specified_product_arm.Product_specification"/> belongs to.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specified_product_arm  Entity: Product_specification  Attribute: defining_specifications 
   <express_ref linkend="specified_product:arm:Specified_product_arm.Product_specification.defining_specifications"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Specified_product_arm.Product_specification.defining_specifications">
the set of instances of <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Specification"/> that discriminate the <express_ref linkend="specified_product:arm:Specified_product_arm.Product_specification"/> within its <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Product_class"/>.
<p>Each element of "defining specifications" shall be associated with a <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Product_class"/> by a <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Class_specification_association"/> with "association type" not equal to 'part usage'. 
The associated <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Product_class"/> shall be either the <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Product_class"/> referred to as "item context" or any higher level <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Product_class"/> related, directly or indirectly, to the <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Product_class"/> referred to as "item context", with instances of <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Product_class_relationship"/> with "relation type" 'hierarchy'.
</p>
	</ext_description>
	<ext_description linkend="Specified_product_arm.Specification_based_product_version">
A <b>Specification_based_product_version</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/> that is defined by a <express_ref linkend="specified_product:arm:Specified_product_arm.Product_specification"/>.
<note number="1">The entity <express_ref linkend="specified_product:arm:Specified_product_arm.Specification_based_product_version"/> may be instantiated jointly with other subtypes of <express_ref linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/>. 
</note>
		<example number="1">
Depending on the specialization of <express_ref linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/>, a <express_ref linkend="specified_product:arm:Specified_product_arm.Specification_based_product_version"/> may identify a part version that provides the design of a manufactured product, a document version that is a realization of a document product or a function version.
</example>
		<note number="2">
The <express_ref linkend="specified_product:arm:Specified_product_arm.Product_specification"/> provides the set of specifications from which the product version shall be designed or manufactured.
</note>
		<example number="2">
A brochure editor may offer to his customers various brochure types with variable paper quality, coloring, layout. 
These concepts can be represented with instances of the entities defined in the "product class" module. Thus, an instance of <express_ref linkend="specified_product:arm:Specified_product_arm.Specification_based_product_version"/> may identify a document version that is the realization of a particular kind of brochure with a particular selection of paper and layout.
</example>
	</ext_description>
	<ext_description linkend="Specified_product_arm.Specification_based_product_version.specification_source">
the <express_ref linkend="configuration_item:arm:Configuration_item_arm.Item_design_association"/> that provides the specifications of the <express_ref linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/>.
</ext_description>
	<ext_description linkend="Specified_product_arm.Specification_based_product_version.wr:WR1">
the <b>Specification_based_product_version</b> shall identify a realization of a <express_ref linkend="specified_product:arm:Specified_product_arm.Product_specification"/>.
</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>
